cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM

This paper involves generating synthetic X-ray images from body surface geometry, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) techniques. The approach also involves learning networks to predict the parameters and full image, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Finally, the framework can be used for image completion and anomaly detection, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) category.
